reviews.text: Comfortable, food & price are ok
Ordinary fast food. Reasonable price. Relatively quiet. Good to meet friends. Easily accessible
Up to standard Cha Chaan Ten quality but the portion is big. The afternoon tea set is value for money

Just your run of the mill Hong Kong style café. Plenty of selections, can't say for the others but what I had was average at best. Just a meal to get your dinner over with when you just wanna eat and go home. The pork chop had too much fat, in fact it felt like I was eating fat more than meat. Curry was the typical Hong Kong curry that is more sweet than spicy.

One waitress, a middle aged lady was pretty nice. The kind you feel like your old aunt is making sure you're comfortable having your meal. So this is a plus point, thus an extra star.
This restaurant have many choice of dim sum.Enjoy and good taste
